FBIS3-15054 "drsov041_b_94022" FBIS-SOV-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Chernomyrdin Returns to Duty After Illness LD0203115994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 2 Mar 94 LD0203115994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Viktor Chernomyrdin returned to his duties as prime minister today after a week-long absence due to illness, Valentin Grishin [name as heard], first deputy head of the Russian Government's press service, has announced. Viktor Chernomyrdin is today preparing for tomorrow's government sitting, which is to examine the draft budget of the Russian Federation for this year, and also for an expanded government sitting scheduled for 4 March. A traditional weekly working meeting with Boris Yeltsin is scheduled for 1400, after which talks will be held with Uzbekistan's President Islam Karimov, followed by the signing of a package of Russian-Uzbek documents.
